        <h1 style="font-size:200%;text-align:center">Standard-Winged Nightjar</h1>
    </div>
  <div class="panel">
    <img style="width:100%;" src="standardwingednightjar.png" alt="Standard-Winged Nightjar">
    <p>Lifespan: 4 years</p>
    <p>Top speed: About 30 mph
    <p>Weight: 32-65 grams</p>
    <p>Diet: Insects, including moths, beetles, grasshoppers, and winged ants, which it catches in flight</p>
    <p>Predators: Birds of prey, including bat hawks</p>
    <p>Range: Sahel region of Africa</p>
    <p>Conservation Status: Least concern>
    <div class="panel2">
        <p>Fun Fact: During breeding season, the secondary flight feather on males lengthens to trail behind them.</p>
    </div>
        <div class="panel4">
        <p>Fun Fact: Their genus name, caprimulgus, means "goat milker" in Latin, referring to a myth that nightjars would suck milk from goats.</p>
